===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=颈|alt=頚,𩒍,𩒤,𧯬}}

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} compares this to {{cog|bo|སྐེ||neck}}, {{cog|cdm|केक्‌|tr=kek||neck}}, {{m|cdm|कय्‍क्‌|tr=kəyk||neck, stem}}, and suggests that this word is part of a larger word family based on a {{cog|sit}} root {{m|und|*ke||concave}}. These {{cog|tbq}} comparanda are given under {{cog|tbq-pro|*s/m-kej-k||neck}} in STEDT.

{{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} relates this to {{och-l|亢|id=1|neck}}, but {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} finds this relationship unlikely.

